# Local dev (`npm run dev`) reads .env: a relative path proxied by Vite
# (see vite.config.js `server.proxy`) to https://api.hlohealth.in, which
# avoids CORS issues while developing.
#
# Production builds (`npm run build`) read .env.production instead, since
# Vite's dev-server proxy does not exist in the built output — that file
# must point at the real, absolute API origin directly.
#
# IMPORTANT: for the production build to actually work once deployed,
# https://api.hlohealth.in must send Access-Control-Allow-Origin for
# whatever domain serves the built frontend (e.g. https://hlohealth.in).
# As of the last check, it does not — this needs a backend-side fix
# independent of anything in this repo.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api
